---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Sections with LaTeX use set:html so Astro doesn't try to parse {} as expressions.
const postDemoHtml = String.raw`
    <!-- ── Why ZK? ── -->
    <h2>Why Is This Zero-Knowledge?</h2>

    <h3>Completeness</h3>
    <p>
      An honest Peggy who truly knows the secret word will always succeed. Whatever side Victor
      calls, she can reach it — directly if she is already there, or through the door otherwise.
      An honest prover always convinces an honest verifier.
    </p>

    <h3>Soundness</h3>
    <p>
      Suppose Peggy is cheating and does not know the secret word. She cannot open the door, so
      she is stuck on whichever path she entered. Victor's call is independent and random —
      there is exactly a $\frac{1}{2}$ probability he calls the side she entered. The probability
      of a cheater surviving one round is therefore $\frac{1}{2}$. After $k$ rounds:
    </p>
    $$P(\text{cheater not caught after } k \text{ rounds}) = \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^k$$

    <h3>Zero-Knowledge</h3>
    <p>
      What does Victor actually learn from a successful round? He shouted a direction, and Peggy
      emerged from that direction. But he could have <em>simulated</em> this entire transcript
      himself — pick a random side (A or B), imagine a person coming from that side, write it down.
      The simulated transcript is statistically indistinguishable from a real interaction.
    </p>
    <p>
      Because Victor could produce the same-looking evidence without ever talking to Peggy,
      the real interaction conveys <strong>zero information</strong> about the secret word.
    </p>

    <div class="callout note">
      <div class="callout-label">Physical Intuition</div>
      This is the beautiful thing about the Ali Baba Cave: you can hold the protocol
      in your head without any cryptography. A child could follow along and understand why
      it works. The magic door is the only cryptographic primitive — and the rest is just
      spatial logic.
    </div>

    <!-- ── Rounds table ── -->
    <h2>How Many Rounds?</h2>
    <p>
      The soundness error is exactly $\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\right)^k$ — far better per-round
      than graph coloring or Sudoku, because there are only two possible challenges.
    </p>
    <table class="math-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Rounds ($k$)</th>
          <th>Soundness error $\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\right)^k$</th>
          <th>Verifier confidence</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>1</td>  <td>50%</td>     <td>50%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>5</td>  <td>3.1%</td>    <td>96.9%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>10</td> <td>0.098%</td>  <td>99.9%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>20</td> <td>$\approx 10^{-4}$%</td><td>$\approx 100\%$</td></tr>
        <tr><td>30</td> <td>$\approx 10^{-7}$%</td><td>$\approx 100\%$</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>
      Twenty rounds push the soundness error below one in a million — far faster convergence
      than the 27-group Sudoku ZKP or even the graph coloring protocol.
      The trade-off: the cave ZKP is pedagogically perfect but not practical for complex statements.
      Real-world ZKPs (zkSNARKs, zkSTARKs) achieve near-zero soundness error in a <em>single
      non-interactive round</em>, using cryptographic hardness rather than repetition.
    </p>

    <div class="page-nav">
      <a href="/chapters/graph-coloring">← Graph Coloring</a>
      <a href="/zkp" class="next">Sudoku →</a>
    </div>
`;
---

<style is:global>
  /* ── Cave SVG ── */
  .cave-wrap svg { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; max-width: 300px; margin: 0 auto; }

  #peggyG { transition: transform 0.75s cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.4, 0.64, 1); }
  #hlA, #hlB { transition: opacity 0.4s ease; }
  #doorGlowEl { transition: opacity 0.35s ease; }
  #callBubble { transition: opacity 0.28s ease; }
  #labelA, #labelB { transition: fill 0.3s ease; }
  #peggyLabel { transition: fill 0.2s ease; }

  @keyframes doorPulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 0.55; }
    50%       { opacity: 1; }
  }
  .door-pulsing { animation: doorPulse 0.85s ease-in-out infinite; }

  /* ── Demo layout ── */
  .cave-demo-body { display: flex; flex-direction: row; align-items: flex-start; gap: 2.5rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  .cave-left  { flex: 0 0 auto; }
  .cave-right { flex: 1; min-width: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.8rem; }

  /* ── Phase bar ── */
  .phase-bar { display: flex; gap: 3px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .phase-step { flex: 1; height: 2px; border-radius: 1px; background: var(--border); transition: background 0.3s; }
  .phase-step.done    { background: var(--muted); }
  .phase-step.current { background: var(--accent); }

  /* ── Info panel ── */
  .info-panel { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.022); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; padding: 0.85rem 1rem; }
  .info-panel-label { font-size: 0.58rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.13em; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }

  /* ── Role badges ── */
  .role-row { display: flex; gap: 0.9rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .role-badge { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.82rem; }
  .role-dot { width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .role-dot.peggy  { background: var(--heading); border: 1.5px solid var(--accent); }
  .role-dot.victor { background: #252534; border: 1.5px solid var(--muted); }

  /* ── Choice reveal ── */
  .choice-display { display: flex; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  .choice-box { flex: 1; padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem; background: var(--bg-code); border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .choice-box-label { font-size: 0.58rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  .choice-box-value { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--heading); }
  .choice-box.hidden .choice-box-value { color: var(--muted); }
  .choice-box.match  { border-color: #4fa870; }
  .choice-box.mismatch { border-color: #c44444; }

  /* ── Verify checks ── */
  .verify-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.83rem; padding: 0.2rem 0; }
  .v-ok   { color: #4fa870; }
  .v-fail { color: #c44444; }

  /* ── Confidence bar ── */
  .conf-bar-wrap { height: 3px; background: var(--border); border-radius: 2px; margin: 0.6rem 0 0.3rem; overflow: hidden; }
  .conf-bar { height: 100%; background: var(--accent); border-radius: 2px; transition: width 0.5s ease; width: 0%; }

  /* ── Mobile ── */
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .cave-demo-body { flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }
    .cave-left { width: 100%; max-width: 280px; }
    .cave-right { width: 100%; }
  }
</style>

<BaseLayout
  title="Ali Baba Cave — ZK Proofs"
  crumb="Protocols · Ali Baba Cave"
  useKatex
  extraScript="/js/alibaba-demo.js"
>
  <div class="content">

    <div class="page-meta">Protocols · Demos</div>
    <h1>The Ali Baba Cave</h1>

    <p>
      The Ali Baba Cave is the most intuitive introduction to zero-knowledge proofs — a physical
      metaphor that makes the abstract idea of "proving without revealing" immediately concrete.
      Originally described by Jean-Jacques Quisquater and others in 1989, it has become the
      canonical first example of a ZKP.
    </p>

    <!-- ── The Story ── -->
    <h2>The Cave</h2>
    <p>
      Imagine a cave shaped like a ring, with a single entrance at the front. Inside, the ring
      splits into two corridors: <strong>Path A</strong> on the left and <strong>Path B</strong>
      on the right. Both paths lead to the same inner chamber, separated by a magic door in the
      middle. The door can only be opened by someone who knows the secret word.
    </p>
    <p>
      From the outside, you can only see the entrance — you cannot tell which path anyone
      inside has taken.
    </p>

    <!-- ── Setup ── -->
    <h2>The Setup</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Peggy (Prover)</strong> — knows the secret word that opens the magic door.</li>
      <li><strong>Victor (Verifier)</strong> — wants to be convinced Peggy knows the word, without
          learning the word himself.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- ── Protocol ── -->
    <h2>The Protocol</h2>
    <p>Each round of the proof has three steps.</p>

    <h3>Step 1 — Peggy Enters</h3>
    <p>
      Victor waits outside. Peggy walks into the cave and randomly goes down <em>either</em>
      path A or path B. Victor cannot see which one she chose.
    </p>

    <h3>Step 2 — Victor Calls</h3>
    <p>
      Victor walks to the entrance (but not inside) and shouts which side he wants Peggy
      to come back from: <em>"Come out from A!"</em> or <em>"Come out from B!"</em> — chosen
      randomly with equal probability.
    </p>

    <h3>Step 3 — Peggy Exits</h3>
    <p>
      If Peggy is already on the called side, she simply walks back out. If she is on
      the <em>opposite</em> side, she uses the magic door to cross to the other path and then
      exits. Either way, she emerges from the correct side.
    </p>
    <p>
      A cheater who doesn't know the secret word is stuck on whichever path they entered.
      They can only hope that Victor calls the side they happen to be on — a 50% gamble each round.
    </p>

    <!-- ── Try It ── -->
    <h2>Try It Yourself</h2>
    <p>
      Step through the protocol below. You play both Peggy and Victor — watching the same events
      from both perspectives simultaneously.
    </p>

    <figure>
    <section class="demo-section" id="caveDemo" aria-label="Interactive Ali Baba Cave demo">
      <div class="demo-inner">

        <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; gap:1rem; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:1rem;">
          <div>
            <span class="demo-eyebrow">Interactive Demo</span>
            <div class="demo-title">The Ali Baba Cave</div>
            <p class="demo-desc" id="demoMsg">Click <strong>Begin Round</strong> to start.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="demo-stats" style="margin:0; border:none; padding:0; gap:1.5rem; flex-shrink:0;">
            <div class="demo-stat">
              <div class="demo-stat-value" id="statRounds">0</div>
              <div class="demo-stat-label">Rounds</div>
            </div>
            <div class="demo-stat">
              <div class="demo-stat-value" id="statConf">—</div>
              <div class="demo-stat-label">Confidence</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="phase-bar">
          <div class="phase-step current" id="ps0"></div>
          <div class="phase-step" id="ps1"></div>
          <div class="phase-step" id="ps2"></div>
          <div class="phase-step" id="ps3"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="cave-demo-body">

          <div class="cave-left">
            <div class="cave-wrap">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 300 268" aria-label="Cave diagram showing paths A and B">
                <defs>
                  <filter id="softGlow" x="-60%" y="-60%" width="220%" height="220%">
                    <feGaussianBlur stdDeviation="5" result="blur"/>
                    <feMerge>
                      <feMergeNode in="blur"/>
                      <feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/>
                    </feMerge>
                  </filter>
                  <radialGradient id="rockGrad" cx="38%" cy="30%" r="68%">
                    <stop offset="0%"   stop-color="#1c1c28"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#0e0e14"/>
                  </radialGradient>
                  <radialGradient id="caveGrad" cx="50%" cy="45%" r="55%">
                    <stop offset="0%"   stop-color="#0e0e18"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#080810"/>
                  </radialGradient>
                </defs>

                <path fill-rule="evenodd"
                      d="M 268,118 A 118,98 0 1 0 32,118 A 118,98 0 1 0 268,118 Z
                         M 205,113 A 55,65 0 1 0 95,113 A 55,65 0 1 0 205,113 Z"
                      fill="url(#caveGrad)" stroke="#1c1c2a" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <ellipse cx="150" cy="113" rx="55" ry="65"
                         fill="url(#rockGrad)" stroke="#20202e" stroke-width="1"/>
                <ellipse cx="150" cy="117" rx="88" ry="73" fill="none" stroke="#0f0f18" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.7"/>
                <ellipse cx="150" cy="115" rx="75" ry="61" fill="none" stroke="#0f0f18" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5"/>

                <path id="hlA"
                      d="M 150,216 A 118,98 0 1 0 150,20 L 150,48 A 55,65 0 1 1 150,178 Z"
                      fill="rgba(100,140,220,0.18)" opacity="0"/>
                <path id="hlB"
                      d="M 150,216 A 118,98 0 1 1 150,20 L 150,48 A 55,65 0 1 0 150,178 Z"
                      fill="rgba(100,140,220,0.18)" opacity="0"/>

                <rect x="134" y="207" width="32" height="62" fill="#111113"/>
                <line x1="134" y1="207" x2="134" y2="234" stroke="#222232" stroke-width="2"/>
                <line x1="166" y1="207" x2="166" y2="234" stroke="#222232" stroke-width="2"/>
                <path d="M 134,207 Q 150,201 166,207" fill="none" stroke="#222232" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <line x1="134" y1="234" x2="166" y2="234" stroke="#1c1c2c" stroke-width="1"/>
                <text x="150" y="249" text-anchor="middle" fill="#303050" font-size="7" font-family="monospace" letter-spacing="2" opacity="0.7">ENTRY</text>

                <rect x="140" y="41" width="20" height="14" fill="#111113"/>
                <rect x="137" y="37" width="26" height="22" rx="3" fill="#131320" stroke="#2c2c44" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <path d="M 138,44 Q 150,37 162,44" fill="none" stroke="#2c2c44" stroke-width="1.2"/>
                <rect x="139" y="45" width="9" height="10" rx="1" fill="none" stroke="#222235" stroke-width="0.8"/>
                <rect x="152" y="45" width="9" height="10" rx="1" fill="none" stroke="#222235" stroke-width="0.8"/>
                <circle cx="159" cy="52" r="2.2" fill="#282840"/>
                <ellipse id="doorGlowEl" cx="150" cy="48" rx="24" ry="15"
                         fill="rgba(129,140,248,0.55)" opacity="0" filter="url(#softGlow)"/>
                <text x="150" y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="#303050" font-size="7" font-family="monospace" letter-spacing="2" opacity="0.7">DOOR</text>

                <text id="labelA" x="57" y="123" text-anchor="middle" fill="#2c2c48" font-size="22" font-weight="700" font-family="monospace">A</text>
                <text id="labelB" x="243" y="123" text-anchor="middle" fill="#2c2c48" font-size="22" font-weight="700" font-family="monospace">B</text>

                <g transform="translate(150, 255)">
                  <circle r="11" fill="#12121c" stroke="#2e2e48" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                  <text text-anchor="middle" dy="4.5" fill="#818cf8" font-size="11" font-weight="700" font-family="monospace">V</text>
                </g>

                <g id="callBubble" opacity="0" transform="translate(150, 255)">
                  <polygon points="-5,-18 5,-18 0,-11" fill="#1c1c32" stroke="#818cf8" stroke-width="1" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                  <rect x="-38" y="-48" width="76" height="29" rx="6" fill="#1c1c32" stroke="#818cf8" stroke-width="1.2"/>
                  <text id="callText" x="0" y="-30" text-anchor="middle" fill="#ececf4" font-size="12" font-weight="700" font-family="monospace">Path A!</text>
                </g>

                <g id="peggyG" style="transform: translate(150px, 233px);">
                  <circle id="peggyCircle" r="11" fill="#181828" stroke="#818cf8" stroke-width="2"/>
                  <text id="peggyLabel" text-anchor="middle" dy="4.5" fill="#ececf4" font-size="11" font-weight="700" font-family="monospace">P</text>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cave-right">

            <div id="panelIdle">
              <div class="info-panel">
                <div class="info-panel-label">Protocol Roles</div>
                <div class="role-row">
                  <div class="role-badge">
                    <div class="role-dot peggy"></div>
                    <span><strong>P</strong> = Peggy (Prover) — knows the secret word</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="role-badge">
                    <div class="role-dot victor"></div>
                    <span><strong>V</strong> = Victor (Verifier) — waits outside</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <p style="font-size:0.82rem; color:var(--muted); margin-top:0.7rem; line-height:1.65;">
                  The magic door in the centre connects Path A and Path B.
                  Only someone who knows the secret word can pass through it.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="panelInside" style="display:none;">
              <div class="info-panel">
                <div class="info-panel-label">Peggy's Secret Choice</div>
                <div class="choice-display">
                  <div class="choice-box" id="choiceBox">
                    <div class="choice-box-label">Path taken</div>
                    <div class="choice-box-value" id="choiceValue">—</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="choice-box hidden" style="flex:2;">
                    <div class="choice-box-label">Victor's view</div>
                    <div class="choice-box-value" style="color:var(--muted); font-size:0.8rem; line-height:1.5;">
                      Victor waits outside.<br>He cannot see which path<br>Peggy chose.
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="panelCalled" style="display:none;">
              <div class="info-panel" style="margin-bottom:0.7rem;">
                <div class="info-panel-label">Victor's Challenge</div>
                <div class="choice-display">
                  <div class="choice-box" id="peggyBox">
                    <div class="choice-box-label">Peggy is on</div>
                    <div class="choice-box-value" id="peggyBoxVal">—</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="choice-box" id="victorBox">
                    <div class="choice-box-label">Victor calls</div>
                    <div class="choice-box-value" id="victorBoxVal">—</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="info-panel" id="doorPanel">
                <div class="info-panel-label">What Peggy must do</div>
                <p id="doorNote" style="font-size:0.82rem; line-height:1.65; color:var(--text); margin:0;"></p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="panelExited" style="display:none;">
              <div class="info-panel">
                <div class="info-panel-label">Round Result</div>
                <div class="verify-row v-ok" id="resultRow">
                  <span style="font-size:0.95rem;">✓</span>
                  <span id="resultText"></span>
                </div>
                <div class="conf-bar-wrap">
                  <div class="conf-bar" id="confBar"></div>
                </div>
                <p style="font-size:0.7rem; color:var(--muted); margin:0; line-height:1.5;">
                  Probability that Peggy knows the secret (assuming she could be cheating)
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="demo-actions" style="margin-top:1.2rem;">
          <button class="demo-action-btn" id="actionBtn" onclick="handleAction()">Begin Round</button>
          <button class="demo-again-btn" id="resetBtn" onclick="resetDemo()" style="display:none;">Reset</button>
        </div>

      </div>

      <p class="demo-caption">
        <strong>Figure 3.</strong> &ensp;Interactive simulation of the Ali Baba Cave zero-knowledge
        proof. Peggy's random path choice is shown to <em>you</em> (the reader) but is invisible to
        Victor. Both parties' perspectives are displayed simultaneously for clarity.
        Original protocol by Jean-Jacques Quisquater et al., 1989.
      </p>
    </section>
    </figure>

    <!-- "Why ZK" and "How Many Rounds" sections contain LaTeX — rendered via set:html -->
    <Fragment set:html={postDemoHtml} />

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
